---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro'
import { Image } from 'astro:assets'
import about from '../images/about.jpg'
import team1 from '../images/team-1.jpg'
import team2 from '../images/team-2.jpg'
import team3 from '../images/team-3.jpg'
---
<MainLayout title='About Herodotus'>
  <h1 class='text-4xl font-medium mb-5'>About Herodotus</h1>
  <div class='flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-6'>
    <div class='w-full md:w-1/2 mb-8 md:mb-0'>
      <Image
        src={about} 
        alt='Herodotus Team' 
        class='w-full h-auto rounded-md shadow-lg'
      >
    </div>
    <div class='w-full md:w-1/2'>
      <h2 class='text-3xl font-medium mb-6'>Who We Are</h2>
      <p class='text-gray-800 leading-relaxed mb-6'>
        Herodotus is a digital haven for developers. We explore programming, web trends, Linux, and tech culture through curated articles and features.
      </p>
      <p class='text-gray-800 leading-relaxed mb-6'>
        From tutorials to workshops, we empower curious minds with practical insights, modern tools, and stories that shape the future of development.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class='mt-10'>
    <h2 class='text-3xl font-medium mb-8'>Our Team</h2>
    <div class='grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8'>
      <div class='bg-gray-50 shadow-lg rounded-md overflow-hidden'>
        <Image
        src={team1} 
        alt='Esbern Mikkelsen' 
        class='w-full h-auto rounded-md shadow-lg'
        />
        <div class='p-6'>
          <h3 class='text-xl font-medium text-gray-800 mb-2'>Esbern Mikkelsen</h3>
          <p class='text-gray-700 mb-2'>Founder & Editor</p>
          <p class='text-gray-700 mb-2'>Esbern is a former systems architect whose career began in the late 1980s writing shell scripts on Unix terminals. As the web emerged, Esbern quietly transitioned from sysadmin to infrastructure sage. He’s mentored generations of developers in the virtues of clean architecture and resilient design.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class='bg-gray-50 shadow-lg rounded-md overflow-hidden'>
        <Image
        src={team2} 
        alt='Christopher McKinlay' 
        class='w-full h-auto rounded-md shadow-lg'
        />
        <div class='p-6'>
          <h3 class='text-xl font-medium text-gray-800 mb-2'>Christopher McKinlay</h3>
          <p class='text-gray-700 mb-2'>Lead Features Editor</p>
          <p class='text-gray-700 mb-2'>Christopher, with his background in C and C++, brings a systems-level rigor to every piece he edits. His fluency in JavaScript and Python frameworks allows him to bridge legacy wisdom with modern web developments. Known for his sharp eye and love of clean syntax, he’s the editorial compass behind Herodotus’ most compelling features.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class='bg-gray-50 shadow-lg rounded-md overflow-hidden'>
        <Image
        src={team3} 
        alt='Lucia Santamaria' 
        class='w-full h-auto rounded-md shadow-lg'
        />
        <div class='p-6'>
          <h3 class='text-xl font-medium text-gray-800 mb-2'>Lucía Santamaria</h3>
          <p class='text-gray-700 mb-2'>Lead Cloud Writer</p>
          <p class='text-gray-700 mb-2'>Lucía's  background is in distributed systems and specialises in the Cloud architectures of AWS, Azure, and Google Cloud. She turns multi-region failovers and IAM policies into tales of resilience and design. Her writing balances technical precision with poetic clarity. Lucía is the team’s go-to for cloud strategy, cost optimisation, and the occasional Terraform incantation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</MainLayout>
